Bonus 2 - Google Sheets API Connection

Business Science

9/2/2020

Step 1 - Open a New Google Sheet

Call it something like Cran API

Step 2 - Decorate your Google Sheet

Minimum Requirements: Make sure to set up cells B4:B7 as shown. These will be mapped to your API URL package, start, end, and by parameters.

Step 3 - Connect your Google Sheet to your API

We need to set your Google Sheet this up in your google sheet.

Open GS Script Editor

Youll open your script editor in Google Sheets by going to Tools > Script Editor. Note - You may need to accept permissions to open up the script editor.

Paste Script

You should now see a Script Editor where you can add code. Ive provided CranAPI.gs. All you need to do is copy and paste into the script editor and save your work. Heres how:

  1. Rename your Script: CranAPI.gs
  2. Paste the contents of the CranAPI.gs file that Ive provided. Make sure to update the awsURL() function to return YOUR EC2 SERVER PUBLIC DNS. Just modify Line 11.
  3. Save your work.

Step 4 - Test Your Google Sheet Out

You should now see a Menu Item called CRAN Downloads. Click Get Package Data. Your sheet should automatically update using the inputs provided in Cells B4:B7.

Going Further - Exploring the Google Sheets Script

I encourage you to explore the script to see if you can figure out how it works. Google has the Google Apps Scripts Documentation, which is how I figured out how to do this tutorial.

Theres also a great tutorial on Google Sheets Scripts here.
